CommonFields.Title: Synthesis of Exfoliated PMMA/Na-MMT Nanocomposites via Soap-Free Emulsion Polymerization
Author: Choi, Yeong Suk
Choi, Min Ho
Wang, Ki Hyun
Kim, Sang Ouk
Kim, Yoon Kyung
Chung, In Jae
CommonFields.Location: Department of Chemical Engineering, Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology, 373-1, Kusung-dong, Yusong-gu, Taejon, Korea

Mixing.Description: under a N2 gas at an ambient temperature
20 g of aqueous solution of initiator (1 wt %) was injected into the reactor via a glass syringe through a septum.

ChooseParameter.Other: After the initial polymerization was completed, 15 g of MMA was fed at the rate of 0.16 cm3/min into the reactor through a septum with a syringe pump.
A small amount of a nanocomposite was extracted for 12 h by using a Soxhlet extraction apparatus with THF to remove oligomers or surfactants.

Transmission_Electron_Microscopy.EquipmentUsed: Philips CM-20 trans- mission electron microscope

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: Tan δ and storage modulus (E′) were obtained by a Rheometric Scientific DMTA4 with a dual cantilever from 30 to 200 °C with a heating rate of 5 °C/min under 0.07% of deformation at 1 Hz of frequency.

Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Equipment: Bomem 102 FT-IR spectrometer with KBr pellets
Fourier_Transform_Infrared_Spectroscopy.Description: A total of 40 scans taken at 4 cm-1 of resolutions were averaged.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: at a room temperature with scanning rate of 2°/min in a 2θ range of 1.5- 10°.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: heating from a room temper- ature to 600 °C with the rate of 10 °C/min under a N2 atmosphere
